### Footnotes

<span id="fn_73"></span>[39:6](jub13.htm#fr_73.md) Cf. Isa. lxiii. 9;

Test. XII. Patr., Judah 25: probably Michael is meant. Note that the
medium of communication is an angel, and cf. Gal. iii. 19 (" The Law . .
. ordained through angels"). Later Judaism rejected this idea.

<span id="fn_74"></span>[39:7](jub13.htm#fr_74.md) *i. e.* not the
Pentateuch, "but a history up to the Messianic Kingdom" (Charles, in
Oxford *Corpus*).

<span id="fn_75"></span>[39:8](jub13.htm#fr_75.md) Read this ver. after
ver. 25.

<span id="fn_76"></span>[40:1](jub13.htm#fr_76.md) Cf. Rev. i. 7 (in the
final theophany).

<span id="fn_77"></span>[40:2](jub13.htm#fr_77.md) Cf. i. 24; Jer. xxxi. i.

<span id="fn_78"></span>[40:3](jub13.htm#fr_78.md) Cf. Isa. xxiv. 23.

<span id="fn_79"></span>[40:4](jub13.htm#fr_79.md) Cf. Exod. xiv. 19.

<span id="fn_80"></span>[40:5](jub13.htm#fr_80.md) From these the angel
dictates to Moses (who writes) the Book of Jubilees.

<span id="fn_81"></span>[40:6](jub13.htm#fr_81.md) Text corrupt. Read "from
the day of creation, till the heavens."

<span id="fn_82"></span>[40:7](jub13.htm#fr_82.md) *i. e.* in the Messianic
Kingdom.

<span id="fn_83"></span>[40:8](jub13.htm#fr_83.md) Cf. Rev. xxii. 2.

